item.title: CVE-2017-0160|2024-08-05T12:55:19.118Z -- microsoft%20corporation -- .net%20framework
item.description: Microsoft .NET Framework 2.0, 3.5, 4.5.2, 4.6, 4.6.1, 4.6.2 and 4.7 allows an attacker with access to the local system to execute malicious code, aka ".NET Remote Code Execution Vulnerability."
